SIMPLE: disinfectant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: disinfectant
<hw>dis`in*fect"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which
disinfects, especially an agent for killing or removing the
microorganisms which cause infection. Commonly used disinfectants are
<examp>chlorine</examp>, <examp>sodium hypochlorite solution</examp>,
<examp>hydrogen peroxide</examp>, and <examp>alcohol</examp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>disinfection</ent>⟦br⟧
